The paper discusses probabilistic models for relational data, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of (conditional) Markov networks and probabilistic inference suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these models for classification tasks, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of relational data also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the use of these models for webpage classification, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of directed models and the advantages of undirected models, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
